briefdescription.para: The root dependency of a cache on its root site.

detaileddescription.para: This may be useful to either include, as when invalidating caches in response to scene edits, or to exclude, as when scanning dependency arcs to compensate for a namespace edit.

briefdescription.para: Purely direct dependencies involve only arcs introduced directly at this level of namespace.
Partly direct dependencies involve at least one arc introduced directly at this level of namespace; they may also involve ancestral arcs along the chain as well.
Ancestral dependencies involve only arcs from ancestral levels of namespace, and no direct arcs.
Virtual dependencies do not contribute scene description, yet represent sites whose scene description (or ancestral scene description) informed the structure of the cache.

detaileddescription.para: One case of this is when a reference or payload arc does not specify a prim, and the target layerStack does not provide defaultPrim metadata either. In that case a virtual dependency to the root of that layer stack will represent the latent dependency on that site's metadata.

Another case of this is "spooky ancestral" dependencies from relocates. These are referred to as "spooky" dependencies because they can be seen as a form of action-at-a-distance. They only occur as a result of relocation arcs.

briefdescription.para: Combined mask value representing both pure and partly direct deps.
Combined mask value representing any kind of dependency, except virtual ones.
Combined mask value representing any kind of dependency.
A classification of PcpPrimIndex->PcpSite dependencies by composition structure.
A typedef for a bitmask of flags from PcpDependencyType.
Returns true if this node introduces a dependency in its PcpPrimIndex, false otherwise.

detaileddescription.para: This is equivalent to PcpClassifyNodeDependency(n) != PcpDependencyTypeNone, but is faster.

briefdescription.para: Classify the dependency represented by a node, by analyzing its structural role in its PcpPrimIndex.

detaileddescription.para: Returns a bitmask of flags from PcpDependencyType.
